ence, one deeply engaged with historical consciousness not as an inevitability of the modern world, but as something to be understood within it.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362717840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503627178423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503627178/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles